      <head>Friedrich Klose</head>
      <div>
        <p>German-Swiss composer who studied with (among others) Bruckner between 1886 and 1889
          (contemporaneously with Schenker). He taught at the Akademie der Tonkunst in Munich
          between 1907 and 1919. A week-long celebration of the composer's work was held in Munich
          in June 1918, at which Schenker's associate <ref cRef="dahms_walter">Walter Dahms</ref> was present. </p>

      </div>
